        <div class="mia">
            <h3>My Name</h3>
            <p><b>Huan</b> <small>[hɔan]</small> is Malaysian Hokkien surname - a rare reading of the common surname <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pan_(surname)" target="_blank">潘</a>.<br><b>József</b> <small>[ˈjoːʒɛf]</small> is a Hungarian name derived from the Hebrew name <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Yosef" target="_blank">יוֹסֵף <i>Yōsef</i></a>.</p>

            <br><p><b>潘</b> is my surname from above.<a href="https://thak.taigi.info/1913KamJitian/chheh/?page=289" target="_blank"><br><b>悅</b></a> has the meaning of happiness. <a href="https://thak.taigi.info/1913KamJitian/chheh/?page=457" target="_blank"><br><b>朗</b></a> holds the idea of brightness and clarity.</p>
        </div>

